🔍 SAP MM Analyst Playbook: From Data → Insights → Predictions

🚀 #Themindsetshift: predict issues before they happen — expiry risk, recall readiness, consumption variance, supplier quality trends, and batch genealogy risks.

This visual breaks down the differences between a reactive analyst and a strategic one.

📊 Key SAP MM tables every analyst should know: Material Master (MARA, MARC, MARD), Inventory & Movements (MSEG, MKPF, MATDOC), Procurement (EKKO, EKPO, EBAN), Batch Management, and Quality Management tables.

💡 6 high-value dashboards for MM + MES integration:
Inventory Health
Batch Traceability
Supplier Performance
Material Shortage Prediction
MES Production Visibility
Purchase Order Risk

🤖 AI-driven analysis vs. traditional: instead of dashboard → user review → investigate, AI detects patterns, predicts risk, and suggests action — turning a "10,000 units in inventory" report into "Material XYZ will stock out in 12 days, expedite PO 45001234."

The best analysts don't just report what happened — they use data, integration, and AI to predict what will happen, so the business can act early, stay compliant, and run smarter.
